<div metal:use-macro="view.layout">
    <div metal:fill-slot="main_content">

        <!-- Page Content -->

        <a name="about"></a>
        <div class="content-section-a  ${view.alternate_row_style()}">

            <div class="container">
                <div class="about-me">
                    <div class="col-sm-3 profile-pic">
                        <img src="/static/img/meta.jpg"
                             class="img img-rounded img-responsive"/>
                    </div>

                    <div class="col-sm-9" info> 
                        <h3>Meta - About This Site</h3>
                        <p> I built this site after completing an online course called <a class="underline_link" href="https://training.talkpython.fm/courses/explore_entrepreneurs/python-for-entrepreneurs-build-and-launch-your-online-business" target="_blank">Python for Entrepreneurs</a> by <a class="underline_link" href="https://twitter.com/mkennedy" target="_blank">Michael Kennedy</a>. I love listening to Michael's podcasts <a class="underline_link" href="https://talkpython.fm/" target=_blank">Talk Python To Me</a> and <a class="underline_link" href="https://pythonbytes.fm/" target="_blank">Python Bytes</a>. The course has all of the information needed to launch a website using python and is presented in an incredibly clean and well though out way. I highly reccomend it to anyone interested in using python for web development. 
                        </p>
                        <br>
                        <p>
                        I want to share my expereince getting this site going and keeping it up so that others interested in building a website can learn from my experience. If you are interested in building a site yourself or learning more about python in general please check out Michael's courses and listen to his podcasts. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>


            </div>
            <!-- /.container -->

        </div>
        <!-- /.content-section-a -->

        <a name="Infrastructure"></a>
        <div class="content-section-a  ${view.alternate_row_style()}">
            <div class="col-sm-4 logo-1-pic">
                        <img src="/static/img/do_logo.png"
                             class="img img-rounded img-responsive"/>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-4 logo-2-pic">
                        <img src="/static/img/ansible_logo.png"
                             class="img img-rounded img-responsive"/>
            </div>

            <div class="col-sm-4 logo-2-pic">
                        <img src="/static/img/github_logo.png"
                             class="img img-rounded img-responsive"/>
            </div>

            <div class="container">
                <div class="site-stuff">
                    <div class="col-sm-12" info> 
                        <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
                        <p>All the content that is being delivered to your browser right now has to come from somewhere. In this case it is coming from a <a class="underline_link" href="https://www.digitalocean.com/" target="_blank"> Digital Ocean </a> server located in San Francisco CA. In this section I will describe the details of renting the virtual private server (VPS), configuring the server and maintaining it. An excellent resource for learning about deploying python web apps is <a class="underline_link" href="https://www.fullstackpython.com/" target="_blank">Full Stack Python</a/> by <a class="underline_link" href="https://twitter.com/mattmakai?lang=en" target="_blank">Matt Makai</a>. </p>
                    </div>
                    <div><i class="devicon-amazonwebservices-original" id="test_this"></i></div>
                </div>


            </div>
